tr.th: Conclusion and Recommendations based on this report and previous findings known to us

tr.td: The patient shows elevated HbA1c, indicating suboptimal long-term glycemic control, and increased cholesterol, LDL, and triglycerides, suggesting a heightened cardiovascular risk. Renal function (urea, creatinine) and electrolytes are within normal limits, and there is no evidence of microalbuminuria. Recommend optimization of diabetes and lipid management, and regular monitoring.
